write_ml_library(25.10)                                write_ml_library(25.10)

Name
       write_ml_library  -  Writes library-related data for JedAI to csv files
       with the specified prefix

Syntax
       write_ml_library

       [-help]

       [-objects <object_list>]

       -prefix <string>

       Writes library-related data for JedAI to csv files with  the  specified
       prefix.  It  includes  data  that  is  library  specific and relates to
       lib_cells, timing_tables, and power_tables.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes the  type  and  default
              information for each write_ml_library parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command

              man write_ml_library.

       -objects <object_list>
              Specifies the list of db object(s) to be dumped, which could in-
              clude one or more of the following values:

              lib_arc   lib_cell   lib_feature   lib_pin  library  library_set
              power_table timing_table

              Use curly braces to enclose multiple values.

              Data_type: tcl_obj, optional

       -prefix <string>
              Specifies the prefix for the output files.

              Data_type: string, required

Example
              * The following command writes library-related data for JedAI to
                csv files with the specified prefix:

                write_ml_library -prefix out/

Related Information
              * init_ml

              * write_ml_design

              * write_ml_timing_graph

              * write_ml_timing_path

